4 D. The State Regents shall implement policies and procedures
4
5 for the administration of this act the Oklahoma Tuition Equalization
5
6 Grant Act. The State Regents shall approve as eligible institutions
6
7 of higher education only those private or independent, not-for-
7
8 profit colleges or universities that are domiciled within this
8
9 state, meet approved program and accreditation standards as
9
10 determined by the State Regents, and are fully accredited by the
10
11 Higher Learning Commission of the North Central Association on
11
12 Colleges and Schools or a national accrediting body recognized by
12
13 the United States Department of Education. To be eligible,
13
14 institutions must shall have been granted not-for-profit status
14
15 granted by the Internal Revenue Service and the U. S. United States
15
16 Department of Education prior to July 1, 2012. Additionally,
16
17 eligible institutions shall adhere to the complaint process policies
17
18 and procedures administered by the State Regents. The State Regents
18
19 shall review and take action, as authorized, on complaints
19
20 concerning eligible institutions. The eligible institutions shall
20
21 include Family of Faith College, Mid-America Christian University,
21
22 Oklahoma Baptist University, Oklahoma Christian University, Oklahoma
22
23 City University, Oklahoma Wesleyan University, Oral Roberts
23
24
24
